<L>__{exterior street near bakery night}
<A>__{they walk quietly melvin still walking with his usual attention to where he steps. carol's pov melvin walking and though we can see an improvement it is still decidedly strange as he conspicuously avoids stepping on the lines.}
<B>__{back to scene}
<A>__{carol sighs. it is the sound of possibilities crashing down. melvin looks at her embarrassed, self conscious his habits making him appear unworthy.}
<C>__{carol}
<P>__{(gently; almost lovingly)}
<D>__{i'm sorry, melvin but whatever this is is not going to work.}
<B>__{on melvin}
<A>__{he takes this hard. it forces him to half whisper something he hasn't at all said to himself... given his history... this is an extraordinary intimacy.}
<C>__{melvin}
<D>__{i'm feeling... i've been feeling better.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{melvin, even though it may seem that way now you don't know me all that well...}
<P>__{(as he scoffs)}
<D>__{i'm not the answer for you.}
